# Force LF on CI scripts so they execute on the Ubuntu runner (CRLF breaks the
# shebang + bash parsing). Applies regardless of the committer's autocrlf.
*.sh   text eol=lf
*.py   text eol=lf
*.yml  text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf

# Unity Package Manager rewrites Packages/packages-lock.json on project
# open/bootstrap (it re-resolves the dependency graph + writes the file with LF).
# The committed blob is LF, but with core.autocrlf=true git checks the file out
# as CRLF, so the worktree copy diffs against the LF blob → a phantom ` M` that
# dirties the worktree EVERY bootstrap, blocking serve_soak's clean-tree
# pre-flight (86cacvhc6). Pinning `eol=lf` stops autocrlf from converting it to
# CRLF in the worktree, so the worktree stays LF == the LF-committed blob → no
# recurring churn (no renormalization commit needed; content is fully derived
# from manifest.json so the committed copy stays stable across machines).
Packages/packages-lock.json text eol=lf

# Ops watchdog scripts run under Windows Task Scheduler via powershell.exe on the
# runner machine, so the working-copy encoding must be CRLF to match what the
# scheduled task actually executes (autocrlf normalization would otherwise leave
# the on-disk file diverging from the committed blob, and the PR-body sha256
# citations wouldn't line up with `git hash-object`). WinPS 5.1 additionally
# requires the .ps1 content stay BOM + pure-ASCII to parse cleanly — see
# tools/ops/runner-disconnect-watchdog-INSTALL.md (86catpwcc follow-up).
*.ps1 text eol=crlf
